latestPosts.caption:
Since lot of you were asking about my transformation journey, here’s how I lost 50+ kgs of body weight. 💫

Prioritise ⤵️ 

1. Strength/ Resistance training at home/gym/ playground - This has nothing to do with lifting heavy weights. Body weight exercises also helps.

2. Cardio to keep up with the heart health & stamina

3. Balanced nutrition- good food, more greens, protein, good fats & good carbs

4. Portion control. Eat until you’re 80% full

5. Limit/ swap refined sugar 

6. Increase water intake

7. Have your dinner early. At least 3-4 hours before your bed time. It helps your digestive system to assimilate nutrients properly 

8. Increase your step counts (Keep it between 8K - 15K)

9. Sleep for 7-8 hours for muscle recovery

I made lot of mistakes in the beginning and didn’t know about the importance of protein rich diet and calories deficit concept. However, I learnt about it & started implementing the basics and could see improvements. 

Having protein rich 🥛🥚🍳 diet helps you retain the muscle mass otherwise which you are prone to lose during weight loss journey.

High fibre diet 🥬 🍎helps with digestion & better absorption of food.

Confused about how to start your fitness journey?
Here’s your blueprint — no more guesswork, just step-by-step progress.

Here’s what you need to do along with exercise 

1. If your goal is to lose fat. Eat in a deficit of 200-300 calories from your maintenance calories.
2. If your goal is to gain muscle mass then eat in a surplus of 200-300 calories from your maintenance calories.
3. Prioritise protein for muscle gain & fibre for gut health
4. Drink 3-4 ltr of water
5. 7-8 hours of deep sleep for recovery 
6. Stay active during the stay- if your goal is to lose fat then focus on getting 10 K steps daily.

Hate eating broccoli? I get it - I have a rescue recipe which is a flavor bomb.

High Protein Broccoli Herby Rice 🥦

Ingredients 
100 g low fat paneer ( I use home made)
200 g Broccoli 
3-4 Garlic
4-5 Almonds
Salt
Frozen corn 1 cup
Half capsicum
1 Onion 
1 green chilli 
4-5 button mushrooms 
Chilli flakes
Oregano 

Recipe 

Take a blender- Add blanched broccoli, low fat paneer, almonds, salt and water to adjust consistency. Blend

Take a pan - add ghee/ oil- add onion, chilli, mushroom, let it cook

Sprinkle salt and add capsicum, and blanched broccoli stems, let it cook.

Add broccoli puree, let it simmer and then add frozen corn, chilli flakes and oregano. Let it simmer and then serve hot with rice.
